# gmail-cleanup-agent backend configuration.
#
# This file is auto-loaded by `python -m gmail_cleanup` at startup.
# Copy it to `config/backend.env` and uncomment / edit the section for
# the backend you want to use. Shell-exported env vars override what's
# in this file, so one-off runs can still set per-invocation overrides
# without editing the file.
#
# Pick exactly ONE of the four backend sections below. Comment out the
# others.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend A — Ollama (recommended for local-LLM runs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tradeoffs: tightest integration with this project, no extra deps
# beyond the base requirements, model lives in Ollama's registry.
# Friendly sampler defaults — no DRY, smaller repeat-penalty window —
# so verbatim-reproduction tasks (which this classifier is) are
# reliable across quant levels.
#
# GCA_BACKEND=ollama
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3:8b              # or whatever you `ollama pull`ed

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend B — OpenAI-compatible (LM Studio / llama.cpp / vLLM / real OpenAI)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tradeoffs: works with anything speaking the OpenAI Chat Completions
# wire format. For local runs you'll point OPENAI_BASE_URL at your
# server and OPENAI_API_KEY is a placeholder. For real OpenAI, use
# your actual key. See docs/llama-server-setup.md if your backend is
# llama.cpp — there are gotchas (reasoning models, sampling configs
# tuned for chat that break verbatim tasks, `--parallel N` slowdowns)
# worth knowing about before a real run.
#
# GCA_BACKEND=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...                              # real key for OpenAI; placeholder ("not-needed") for local
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1          # or http://localhost:1234/v1 (LM Studio), :8080/v1 (llama.cpp), etc.
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini                           # for local servers: exact id from /v1/models
# OPENAI_MAX_TOKENS=4000
# OPENAI_TEMPERATURE=0.1
# OPENAI_JSON_MODE=1                                 # 0 if your local server doesn't accept response_format
# OPENAI_DISABLE_THINKING=0                          # set to 1 for Qwen3, DeepSeek-R1, other reasoning models on llama.cpp
# OPENAI_RETRIES=5

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend C — Anthropic Claude
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tradeoffs: highest classification quality (per cost-math.md), full
# managed API, costs ~$70 on Claude Haiku 4.5 for a 313k-thread run.
# Requires `pip install '.[claude]'` (or `pip install anthropic`).
#
# GCA_BACKEND=claude
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# CLAUDE_MAX_TOKENS=4000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - For DEBUGGING what the agent actually saw at startup, run any
#   command with `-v` (verbose). The backend banner in the log will
#   confirm which backend resolved + base URL / host / model.
# - `config/backend.env` is gitignored — populated copies stay local.
#   `config/backend.env.example` (this file) is checked in.
# - If you want zero file footprint and prefer pure shell, you can
#   still export the same vars before invoking the CLI; shell exports
#   win over the file.
